runs.comm: pitched up on off stump, defended
pitched up again and clipped to midwicket - no run
slightly shorter, driven to cover
full, straight, played back to the bowler

got him, bowled through the gate! Santokie shuffled in, sent the ball down on middle, right up in the blockhole, Warner played across the line and the stumps are pegged back. Australia's danger man up top is gone!
loses his line down the leg side
full in length, on off, clipped to cover
flattish, on the stumps, defended into the leg side
wicket to wicket, Watson goes back and defends
tossed up wide of off stump, rocks back and slaps forcefully behind point for the first runs off the bat
on the stumps, flighted, driven back to the bowler
dragged shorter, pulled through midwicket
short of a length again, pulled to deep square leg
back of a length, wide of off, touch of swing away, Hussey misses with a cut stroke
slower, tossed up on the stumps and drifting out slightly, played back down the pitch
room outside off, driven to mid-off
angled across, fullish, drives and gets an outside edge to third man
fuller, drifting across the right-hander, driven to the man at cover
pitched up on the legs - cutting his fingers over the ball to take the pace off - but Watson fetches it into the crowd at deep midwicket, a lovely clean hit, whipping his wrists through the ball
tossed up, on the stumps, played short on the off side
slanted across and Hussey swings his arms through the ball, the cut shot bringing him runs behind point
length, outside off, not much spin and Watson flat-bats a sweep in front of the man on the deep midwicket boundary
flighted, beats the attempted cut shot, Baugh breaks the bails as Watson stumbles back ... but his foot was grounded
on the stumps, clipped short to mid-on and Sammy's throw to the non-striker's end hits Narine on the toe as he takes evasive action
tossed up outside off, bottom-edged into the ground by Hussey
dabbed to short third man from outside off - but Mathurin had overstepped
flat arm action, pitched up, just where Watson wants it and he launches a big swipe over deep midwicket. Costly overstep, that
on the stumps, goes for a sweep, comes off the thigh pad to short third man
pulled through midwicket
on the stumps, leading edge back to the bowler
shorter, pulled flat to long-on
spears it down the leg side
on the stumps and turns Hussey around, the ball popping off the bat into the off side

pitched up outside off, Watson stays in his crease, leans out and spanks the ball back over long-on for six more. Not enough pace to trouble the batsmen and the swing seems to have disappeared for Santokie
pitched up, driven and Santokie deflects the ball on to the stumps ... Hussey was back though
full, on the leg stump, scooped high over deep midwicket. Watson has taken a liking to Santokie's slightly odd style of delivery ...
slanted across, steered to third man
touch shorter, outside off, cut to the man at point
loses his line down leg and the batsman shovels the ball over deep square leg for another boundary - 17 off the over and Santokie's aura has rapidly disappeared
length, outside off and skidding through, Watson plays to cover
tight line outside off, gets a bit of unexpected bounce and beats Watson's cut, excellently taken by Baugh
drifts on to the legs and clipped through midwicket
angled across on a length, cut for one
touch shorter and Watson seizes on the delivery to cut fiercely behind point for four
length, little bit of away movement, Watson goes down on one knee and punches to cover
on the stumps, turning across, edged on to the pads
shorter length, pulled through midwicket
leg-stump doosra, dabbed into the on side
tossed up, Watson backs away and hammers the ball back to the bowler
length, outside off, worked to midwicket
on the stumps, Watson plays back and clips into the on side
wicket to wicket, turned square on the leg side
slower ball, on off stump and Hussey picks it out of the bowler's hands, booming an aerial drive over long-off
slanted across the batsman, leans out and glides a shot past short third man to the rope
around the wicket, pitched up and driven to cover
length ball outside off, pushed through point
touch short, Watson steps out and cuts hard but straight to point, who saves a run
flighted on the stumps, driven down the ground
tossed up, drifting in, Watson sweeps square
Hussey goes back deep in the crease and chops a doosra down the wicket from outside off
tossed up outside off, guided to short third man
flatter, spinning in, Watson tries to pull forcefully but only succeeds in thumping the ball into his own thigh
tossed up on the stumps, hitting the pad as Watson presses forward - Narine appeals but he's a lone voice
full pitched, Hussey leans out and slices a top edge down to third man, who fields on the bounce
back of a length, guided from outside off stump fine down to third man where Sunil Narine makes a diving stop
leg-stump line, full length, driven coming forward down to long-on
length ball, whipped from off stump through square on the leg side
back of a length, on the stumps, fiddled to point off the back foot
pitched up on off stump, clipped through midwicket
length, on the stumps, flicked off the hips to square leg
length ball, angled across and dropped to point, they sneak a single
length outside off, taking the pace off ... but Watson finds the gap between point and short third man to guide the ball to the boundary and go past fifty
drops short and, quick as you like, Watson swivels to pull square on the leg side
medium pace, angled in from wide of the stumps, blocked back to the bowler
speared in on the full and Watson dismissively chips the ball high over deep midwicket for another maximum
length, on the stumps, Hussey reverses his stance and flips the ball high over the head of short third man for a couple
dragged shorted, on the legs, nudged behind square
high arm action, flat delivery, full ... and spanked over deep midwicket, the ball towering over the boundary for six

shorter this time and Watson gets under it, looping the ball high out to deep midwicket again but this time it's not got the legs and Kieron Pollard pouches. West Indies get the breakthrough they need - but is it too late?
flat, on the legs, nudged square
on the stumps, chopped through midwicket for one
length, clipped through the leg side
pitched up on the stumps, drilled through midwicket and Mathurin, cat-like, pounces on it to prevent a boundary - they don't even get one. Top stop
tip and run short of point, Sammy's pick up isn't clean and Bailey gets home
excellent slower ball, Bailey goes for an agricultural hoick over the leg side and misses completely
length, on the stumps, jabbed to midwicket
length delivery outside off, taking the pace off, steered to short third man and they take one
wicket to wicket, flicked square on the leg side
flat, on the stumps, Hussey rolls the wrists and pulls to deep square leg
room outside off, dabbed on the back foot through point
dragged short, on the pads, nudged through the leg side
angled into the stumps, dropped to short third man
on the legs, punched to the sweeper on the square boundary - that's six of ones and half a dozen of the over
slightly back of a length, Hussey gives himself room and smears a flat six down the ground over long-on. BOOM!
around the wicket, defended on the back foot
pitched up on off, crunched in front of midwicket for one
slower yorker, dug out wide of mid-on, Bravo goes after it himself and they keep the damage down to a single
full and wide, cut hard to the deep square boundary
length, outside off, again rolling his fingers over it, steered on the back foot down to third man
full, hacked to long-on for one
angled across, Hussey opens the face and glides the ball on its way for a boundary that takes him to a typically efficient half-century
around the wicket, slower ball, rolls his fingers over it, Hussey drives in the air - and Sammy drops a simple catch at cover!
length, pushed down the ground
sliding down the leg side and deposited over midwicket, the ball hustling off to the rope unimpeded
low full toss on the legs and swept hard, Pollard fielding with his feet - and almost losing his trousers - out on the boundary
flighted outside off, feathered to third man
tossed up on the wicket, blocked back to the bowler
shorter ball, pulled wide of long-on
flighted across the left-hander, nurdled behind point
length, on the legs, Bailey sweeps hard and flat out to deep backward square
length, spinning across Hussey, who expertly steers the ball fine down to the third man boundary - Australia are almost home, despite Narine's tidy figures
clubbed hard through midwicket for four - and that is that
